Archives
 LOOSE CHANGE
																								 Franklin Templeton Mutual Fund has launched an open-ended equity scheme called Franklin Asian Equity Fund, which will invest in Asian companies, except Japan. The new fund offer closes on December 18 and the minimum investment is Rs 5,000. The fund proposes to invest at least 60 per cent of the corpus at any given time in stocks of overseas companies and a maximum of 40 per cent in Indian companies. Hence, an investor in the fund will not be able to get the tax benefit on long-term capital gains. 																								 Sundaram BNP Paribas Mutual Fund has come out with a thematic equity fund  Energy Opportunity Fund. The three-year close-ended fund will be open till December 11 and the minimum investment amount is Rs 5,000. The fund, which will automatically be converted into an open-ended one after the initial three years, will invest at least 65 per cent of the corpus in the energy sector. 																								 UTI Mutual Fund has introduced a three-year close-ended equity scheme called UTI Infrastructure Advantage Fund Series I. The new offer closes on December 19. The fund house has an open-ended infrastructure fund that has given a return of more than 76 per cent in the past 12 months.
